    <ol>
        <li>Once all TC1 checks have been fulfilled for a manuscript and it is ready to proceed to TC1 complete, or the manuscript is desk-rejected or withdrawn at TC1, log in to the randomization engine website (<a href="https://ecrf1.clinicaltrials.ed.ac.uk/iicarus">https://ecrf1.clinicaltrials.ed.ac.uk/iicarus</a>).
        </li>
        <li>Click “<strong>Status</strong>” at the top of the page.</li>

        <li>In the “<strong>MS Number</strong>” box, enter the manuscript number and click “<strong>Search</strong>”</li>

        <li>On the far right of the search result, click “<strong>Edit</strong>”</li>

        <li>On the next page, select the <strong>TC1 Status</strong>:
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Pass TC1</strong> if the manuscript passed TC1 and sent to subscan</li>
                        <li><strong>Rejected at TC1</strong> if the manuscript was desk-rejected prior to subscan
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Withdrawn at TC1 </strong>if the authors chose to withdraw prior to subscan </li>
                    </ul>
        </li>
        <li>You do not need to enter any comments.</li>
        <li>Select the Checklist Compliance if drop-down is present (it will not be for some mss). 
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Yes</strong> if the authors uploaded the ARRIVE checklist after the sendback</li>
                                    <li><strong>No</strong> if the authors did not upload the checklist</li>
                                    <li><strong>N/A - Ms withdrawn</strong> if the manuscript was withdrawn at TC1 prior to subscan</li>
                                </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Be sure never remove the ARRIVE flag after it has been added, as this is how papers will be tracked through to acceptance. </li>

    </ol>
